author: Lynda Brendish
title: Kate Middleton Competes Against Prince William and Prince Harry During Charity Race -- See the Royals in Action
text:
It wasn't exactly a runaway bride scenario, but this weekend Kate Middleton put in a pretty good effort at outrunning her husband, Prince William, in the name of charity. WATCH: Kate Middleton and Sister Pippa Were the Most Adorable Bridesmaids in the '90s 
The Duchess of Cambridge turned up to a training day for runners taking part in the London Marathon, which this year benefits Heads Together, a mental health campaign spearheaded by the two royals along with Prince Harry.
The Duchess of Cambridge chats to marathon world record holder Paula Radcliffe & @BBCR1 presenter @AdeleRoberts #headstogether pic.twitter.com/bTtdwWTWPL 
— Kensington Palace (@KensingtonRoyal) February 5, 2017 Prince Harry's years of military service obviously served him well as he easily beat out William and Kate in the fun 100-meter sprint at London's Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park.

Getty Images
And they're off... #headstogether pic.twitter.com/JZ3SvfgnUb 
— Kensington Palace (@KensingtonRoyal) February 5, 2017 NEWS: Prince William and Kate Middleton Will Move to London as George and Charlotte Start School 
The 35-year-old Middleton may have lost the race, but she won the style game, as per usual, looking chic and graceful in skinny black jeans and a red ski jacket, with her hair pulled back in a ponytail.

Getty Images
